 evil game, its a fact!  I mean, I've killed double the children I did before I started playing!  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=embrael@thesaryrntavern>Embrael</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:pink;'>Tavern Floor Sweeper</span></span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(6/20/03 9:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3321.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> My Reply</span><hr size=1> I just finished reading your short report on Everquest, and think that I'm certainly not going to be the first to say this, but you've left out some vital points about the game and have instead skewed the entire game into something its not. <br>
For one, you've completely ignored the important, helpful and fully healthy emotional link that people have built through this game, and build every day. Friendships and relationships, on a personal level, as well as huge guilds are created and kept together by people who join the game every day for companionship and fun. I can think of nothing better for the people that were suggested in your report to have a higher chance of getting addicted to Everquest. Can you?<br>
Secondly, yes, there are rumors about Everquest leading to many marrital problems, and giving an outlet to people who are sadly unstable and unable to cope with the world to escape to an unhealthy degree, ending their lives when something that seems insurmountable occurs. I feel, as do many, that this would happen if they were doing anything, not simply gaming. <br>
<br>
What bothers me most is that the whole thrust of this article focuses on the overwhelming amount of hours one plays the game. However, Im willing to bet that millions of americans do other similar activies that they find enjoyable for at least that much time daily, or would if they had the opportunity. One does not tell someone he has a serious, dangerous addiction when he watches sports on television, or even cheers for his favorite team. Nor do they say so when someone spends vast amounts of time out with friends, just hanging out, having fun. And thats what we're doing here, we're spending time with our friends, doing a lot of exciting and fun stuff! I completely disagree with the whole tone of your article, and hope that perhaps in your next installment, you show the other side of Everquest, where friends and guilds meet, fun is had on a minute by minute basis and the fervent addiction, the malignant evil you seem to think permeates everything about the game does not even exist. <br>
<br>
<br>
~~~<br>
Asshead.<br>
